22 WHEREAS, cancer remains one of the leading causes of death in the
23 United States, with an estimated one million, nine hundred thousand
24 (1,900,000) new cancer cases and over six hundred thousand (600,000) deaths
25 from cancer expected in 2025; and
26
27 WHEREAS, in Arkansas, cancer is the second leading cause of death,
28 impacting thousands of families each year; and
29
30 WHEREAS, National Cancer Control Month is observed each April to raise
31 awareness about cancer prevention, early detection, and treatment options,
32 aiming to reduce cancer-related deaths and improve patient outcomes; and
33
34 WHEREAS, regular cancer screenings, including mammograms,
35 colonoscopies, and cervical cancer screenings, are critical for early
36 detection and successful treatment; and
