2 WHEREAS, healthy lifestyle choices such as avoiding tobacco products,
3 maintaining a balanced diet, engaging in physical activity, and limiting
4 alcohol consumption can significantly reduce the risk of cancer; and
5
6 WHEREAS, the American Cancer Society, the National Cancer Institute,
7 and other health organizations provide education, screenings, and support
8 services for individuals and families affected by cancer; and
9
10 WHEREAS, increasing public awareness and encouraging proactive health
11 measures can lead to earlier diagnoses, more effective treatments, and
12 improved survival rates for Arkansans,
13
14 NOW THEREFORE,
15 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE NINETY-FIFTH GENERAL
16 ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
17
18 THAT the House of Representatives recognize April as National Cancer
19 Control Month in Arkansas and encourage all Arkansans to take proactive steps
20 in cancer prevention, screening, and treatment.
21
22 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that Arkansans are urged to participate in cancer
23 screenings, adopt healthy lifestyle habits, and support organizations
24 dedicated to cancer research, education, and patient care.
25
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that upon adoption, a copy of this resolution be
27 transmitted to Governor Sarah Huckabee Sanders and the Department of Health
28 for appropriate recognition and observance.
